  <section>
    <title>Comments on Homeworks</title>
    <p>Proofs must be rigorous and readable.  Each proof is a peice of <term>technical writing</term> (one the transferrable skills you gain as a mathematics major).  I must be able to follow your thinking; a proof without English is not a proof.</p>
    <p>An example is not a proof.  You cannot prove something by drawing a diagram.</p>
    <p>When grading, I noticed more than one solution that made me think, "I believe I've read this solution before."  I am choosing to explain this away by believing that this is the result of students working together.  If you do work together, be sure to write up a solution in your own words.  If this continues to happen, then I will call people out on their homework; this comes dangerously close to violating the University's policies on Academic Integrity.</p>
  </section>

